title: ICE: checking wfness of `ConstKind::Expr` is unsupported

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust // run-pass #![feature(generic_const_exprs)] #![allow(incomplete_features)] fn zero_init() -> Substs1 where [u8; N + 1]: , { Substs1([0; N + 1]) } struct Substs1([u8; N + 1]) where [(); N + 1]: ; fn substs2() -> Substs1<{ M * 2 }> where [(); { M * 2 } + 1]: , { zero_init::<{ M * 2 }>() } fn substs3() -> Substs1<{ (L - 1) * 2 }> where [(); (L - 1) * 2 + 1]: , { substs2::<{ Substs1([0; N + 1]) }>() } fn main() { assert_eq!(substs3::<2>().0, [0; 3]); } // Test that the ``{ (L - 1) * 2 + 1 }`` bound on ``substs3`` satisfies the // ``{ N + 1 }`` bound on ``Substs1`` ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.67.0-nightly (32e613bba 2022-12-02) binary: rustc commit-hash: 32e613bbaafee1bcabba48a2257b838f8d1c03d3 commit-date: 2022-12-02 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.67.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.4 ``` ### Error output ``` ```
